value.title: Ricky Martin says it's 'super sad' to see fellow Latinos back Donald Trump
value.excerpt: Ricky Martin discussed his support for Joe Biden and the “super sad” prospect of seeing fellow Latinos vote for Donald Trump.

value.title: Rehire Trump as national CEO to continue US economic renaissance: Steve Cortes
value.excerpt: President Trump will continue the thriving economy if re-elected, but Joe Biden threatens a reversal, Trump 2020 campaign senior adviser Steve Cortes told "Fox & Friends."

value.title: Election 6 days away: Biden back in Delaware as Trump heads to Arizona
value.excerpt: President Trump will hold two campaign rallies in the battleground state of Arizona on Wednesday as his Democratic rival Joe Biden, back in his home state of Delaware, hears a briefing from public health officials on the coronavirus pandemic with just six days left until the election.

value.title: Trump Tells Voters To Change Their Votes—But Only A Few States Allow That
value.excerpt: On Twitter, Trump claimed that searches for “can I change my vote” spiked following the last presidential debate.

value.title: Here's a timeline of President Donald Trump's and Dr. Anthony Fauci's relationship

value.title: Winnable but not yet won: Why Joe Biden and Mike Pence are both headed to Iowa this week
value.excerpt: The pair of visits, as well as Trump's rally earlier this month, indicate that both campaigns see the state as winnable but not yet won.

value.title: Trump uses outdated thinking in attempt to woo suburban women: I'm 'getting your husbands back to work'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump offered his latest appeal to suburban women Tuesday evening, promising to get their husbands "back to work" if he's reelected.

value.title: Cook Political Report editor: Time to 'sound the alarm' on Biden's likely victory

value.title: Trump appears to give a pass to the domestic kidnapping plot against Whitmer
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump repeatedly attacked Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer, a Democrat, during his rally in Lansing, Michigan, on Tuesday, at one point taking credit for the FBI thwarting a plot to kidnap her and then immediately downplaying the actual threat that had been posed to Whitmer.

value.title: Does Russia, China, North Korea Want Trump To Win The Election? What Trump Said About Putin, Xi, Kim Jong Un

value.title: Trump Says Kamala Harris 'Won't Be First Woman President,' Rallygoers Demand Ivanka
value.excerpt: Trump said Kamala Harris will "take over" for Biden three weeks into his term if he wins before declaring, "she will not be the first woman president" Tuesday at a Lansing, Michigan campaign event.

value.title: Trump promised massive middle-class tax cuts in 2016. He delivered cuts, not as much on the middle class part

value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely claims Pennsylvanians 'can't go to church'

value.title: Biden makes plea to ‘unite and heal’ the country during stop in Georgia
value.excerpt: Joe Biden, playing offense in a long time red state turned crucial battleground this year, made a closing campaign pitch on Tuesday for national unity to rise above what he called the division President Trump’s sown during his four years in the White House.

value.title: 2020 Election Live Updates: Biden on track for historic California victory, Kamala Harris heads west
value.excerpt: Every pollster expects Joe Biden to win big in California on election night. The question is how big. New polling suggests Biden’s margin could be of historic proportions, possibly the largest in the state in a century.

value.title: Trump already chose Barrett successor on appeals court, confirmation possible regardless of election outcome
value.excerpt: With Justice Amy Coney Barrett now on the Supreme Court, a new vacancy has opened on the 7th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals where she previously sat, and President Trump has already named the person he plans to have replace her on that bench.

value.title: Pence's office says he did not attend swearing-in due to CDC guidelines
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence did not attend Monday night's White House swearing-in ceremony for Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett because he was adhering to US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention guidelines to prevent the spread of the coronavirus, an administration official told CNN.

value.title: Twitter labels Trump post about mail ballots as ‘disputed’ and ‘misleading’
value.excerpt: The president claimed, without evidence, there were “problems and discrepancies” with mail-in ballots “all over the USA.”

value.title: Judge rejects DOJ's attempt to defend Trump in E. Jean Carroll rape defamation lawsuit
value.excerpt: A federal judge on Tuesday denied the Justice Department's effort to intervene in a defamation lawsuit brought against President Donald Trump by a longtime magazine columnist who has alleged he raped her, paving the way for the case to proceed.

value.title: Biden again clarifies oil 'transition' comment, says industry 'not going to go away'
